{:itonami.blueprint/id "cloud-itonami-isic-2640"
 :itonami.blueprint/name "Manufacture of consumer electronics"
 :itonami.blueprint/isic-rev5 "2640"
 :itonami.blueprint/domain :consumer-electronics/manufacturing
 :itonami.blueprint/license "AGPL-3.0-or-later"
 :itonami.blueprint/social-impact [:worker-safety :product-safety :consumer-electrical-safety]
 :itonami.blueprint/governor :consumer-electronics-plant-operations-governor
 :itonami.blueprint/robotics true
 :itonami.blueprint/required-technologies [:robotics :identity :forms :dmn :bpmn :audit-ledger :eda :cae]
 :itonami.blueprint/status :public-oss
 :itonami.blueprint/maturity :implemented
 :itonami.blueprint/implemented-slice
 "ConsumerElecAdvisor ⊣ Consumer Electronics Plant Operations Governor,
 langgraph-clj StateGraph, append-only audit ledger. A plant OPERATIONS
 COORDINATION actor for consumer-electronics manufacturing (SMT/PCB-
 assembly, final-assembly and test lines producing finished televisions,
 audio/video devices, smart speakers, and wearable devices) -- not
 direct SMT/assembly/test-bench-equipment control authority and not
 consumer-electronics-safety-certification authority (e.g. UL/CE/FCC/
 RoHS compliance mark). Four ops (`:log-production-batch` /
 `:schedule-maintenance` / `:flag-safety-concern` /
 `:coordinate-shipment`), all `:effect :propose` only. Twelve concrete
 governor checks elaborate this blueprint's four HARD invariants:
 propose-only effect, closed op allowlist, closed proposal-effect
 allowlist (no direct SMT/assembly/test-bench-equipment control),
 permanent equipment-actuate block, permanent safety-certification-
 authority block (this actor never self-issues a consumer-electronics
 safety compliance mark), independent equipment verification/
 registration before maintenance scheduling, independent batch
 verification/registration before shipment coordination, independent
 shipment-quantity recompute against the batch's own logged production
 quantity, double-schedule guard, product-type validation, dielectric
 (hipot/withstand) safety-test-voltage plausibility validation, and
 defect-rate plausibility validation. Safety-concern flagging (battery-
 safety/electrical-safety/RoHS-compliance concern) ALWAYS escalates to
 a human plant supervisor; `:log-production-batch` is the only op
 eligible to auto-commit, and only at phase 3 when governor-clean."}
